documentType: search warrant execution log and evidence collection records
summary: This document is an FBI search warrant execution log, evidence collection log, and photographic log for the search of Jeffrey Epstein's residence at 9 East 71st Street, New York, NY, on July 6, 2019. It details the execution process, personnel, and a comprehensive list of evidence seized, including photographs, binders, electronic devices, and other items.

events.title: FBI Search of Epstein's New York Residence
events.description: The FBI executed a search warrant at 9 East 71st Street, New York, NY, Jeffrey Epstein's residence. The search team entered, conducted a walk-through, took photographs, sketched the premises, seized numerous items of evidence, and provided a receipt to an individual on-site.

locations: 9 East 71st Street, New York, NY (Jeffrey Epstein's residence)
keyFacts: The FBI executed a search warrant at Jeffrey Epstein's New York City residence (9 East 71st St.) on July 6, 2019.

A vast array of evidence was seized, including binders containing photos/negatives, CDs, a green massage table, a vibrator, a telescope, female torso busts, and various photographs depicting nude/semi-nude females and minors.
The evidence logs indicate the presence of potentially exploitative material, specifically noting photos of 'nude/semi-nude females' and 'nude/semi-nude minors'.
The search was authorized by Magistrate Judge Barbara Moses of the Southern District of New York.
Detailed photographic and sketch documentation of the entire premises was conducted as part of the search.
